message_1:
A math teacher wants to test her student's understanding of outlier detection. She gave a statistics quiz with 10 questions to her class. The scores are as follows:

{80, 90, 85, 75, 95, 100, 70, 82, 76, 165}

Calculate the median, the mean, and the standard deviation of the quiz scores. Is there any outlier in the data? If yes, which score is an outlier?
